### Area

core

### Describe the bug

Offline tokens takes too much time to load causing transaction timeout during startup.


### Version

22.0.1

### Expected behavior

Loading tokens during startup should be faster

### Actual behavior

Its too slow causing transaction timeout when there are large number of sessions (>500K depends on DB tuning as well)

### How to Reproduce?

Create roughly around 500K offline tokens.
Load the tokens during startup

### Anything else?

The issue seems to be due to a code block in JpaUserSessionPersisterProvider.java

`     UserModel user = userSession.getUser();
        if (user != null) {
            model.setUserId(user.getId());
        }
        else if (userSession instanceof PersistentUserSessionAdapter) {
            model.setUserId(((PersistentUserSessionAdapter) userSession).getUserId());
        }
        `
        
        This block is present in the `private PersistentAuthenticatedClientSessionAdapter toAdapter(RealmModel realm, UserSessionModel userSession, PersistentClientSessionEntity entity) {` method
        
Seems like `userSession.getUser()` is being called unnecessarily here.

Changing the code to below should be optimal
`
if (userSession instanceof PersistentUserSessionAdapter) {
    model.setUserId(((PersistentUserSessionAdapter) userSession).getUserId());
}
else {
    UserModel user = userSession.getUser();
    if (user != null) {
        model.setUserId(user.getId());
    }
}
`

