### Area

admin/ui

### Describe the bug

User status is showing in the user data table as "-" when the user is enabled, leading to some confusion in the actual status of the user

### Version

Nightly

### Expected behavior

User status should show something more informative like "Enabled" 

### Actual behavior

Status shows as "-"

### How to Reproduce?

Navigate to user table in keycloak admin UI

### Anything else?

Appears to be an issue with this section of code in UserDataTable component: 

```
const StatusRow = (user: BruteUser) => {
    return (
      <>
        {!user.enabled && (
          <Label key={user.id} color="red" icon={<InfoCircleIcon />}>
            {t("disabled")}
          </Label>
        )}
        {user.bruteForceStatus?.disabled && (
          <Label key={user.id} color="orange" icon={<WarningTriangleIcon />}>
            {t("temporaryLocked")}
          </Label>
        )}
        {user.enabled && !user.bruteForceStatus?.disabled && "—"}
      </>
    );
  };
```
